    <item>
      <title>HTTP Load Balancing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/http-load-balancer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/http-load-balancer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;overview&#34;&gt;Overview  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#overview&#34; title=&#34;Overview&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Load balancing across multiple application instances is a commonly used technique for optimizing resource utilization, maximizing throughput, reducing latency, and ensuring fault‑tolerant configurations.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Watch the &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nginx.com/resources/webinars/nginx-plus-for-load-balancing-30-min/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;F5 NGINX Plus for Load Balancing and Scaling&lt;/a&gt; webinar on demand for a deep dive on techniques that NGINX users employ to build large‑scale, highly available web services.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;NGINX and NGINX Plus can be used in different deployment scenarios as a &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nginx.com/blog/nginx-load-balance-deployment-models/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;very efficient HTTP load balancer&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>TCP and UDP Load Balancing</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/tcp-udp-load-balancer/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/tcp-udp-load-balancer/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;intro&#34;&gt;Introduction  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#intro&#34; title=&#34;Introduction&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.f5.com/glossary/load-balancer&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Load balancing&lt;/a&gt; refers to efficiently distributing network traffic across multiple backend servers.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In F5 NGINX Plus &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx/releases/#r5&#34;&gt;R5&lt;/a&gt; and later, NGINX Plus can proxy and load balance Transmission Control Protocol) (TCP) traffic. TCP is the protocol for many popular applications and services, such as LDAP, MySQL, and RTMP.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In NGINX Plus &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx/releases/#r9&#34;&gt;R9&lt;/a&gt; and later, NGINX Plus can proxy and load balance UDP traffic. UDP (User Datagram Protocol) is the protocol for many popular non-transactional applications, such as DNS, syslog, and RADIUS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>HTTP Health Checks</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/http-health-check/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/http-health-check/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;intro&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; title=&#34;Introduction&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;NGINX and F5 NGINX Plus can continually test your upstream servers, avoid the servers that have failed, and gracefully add the recovered servers into the load‑balanced group.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;prereq&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;For passive health checks, &lt;a href=&#34;https://nginx.org/en/&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINX Open Source&lt;/a&gt; or &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.nginx.com/products/nginx&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;NGINX Plus&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;For active health checks and the &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/monitoring/live-activity-monitoring/&#34;&gt;live activity monitoring dashboard&lt;/a&gt;, NGINX Plus&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;A load‑balanced group of &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/http-load-balancer/&#34;&gt;HTTP upstream servers&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;hc_passive&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;passive-health-checks&#34;&gt;Passive Health Checks  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#passive-health-checks&#34; title=&#34;Passive Health Checks&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;For passive health checks, NGINX and NGINX Plus monitor transactions as they happen, and try to resume failed connections. If the transaction still cannot be resumed, NGINX Open Source and NGINX Plus mark the server as unavailable and temporarily stop sending requests to it until it is marked active again.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>TCP Health Checks</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/tcp-health-check/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/tcp-health-check/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;intro&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#introduction&#34; title=&#34;Introduction&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;NGINX and F5 NGINX Plus can continually test your TCP upstream servers, avoid the servers that have failed, and gracefully add the recovered servers into the load‑balanced group.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&#34;prereq&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prerequisites&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prerequisites&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You have configured an upstream group of TCP servers in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://nginx.org/en/docs/stream/ngx_stream_core_module.html#stream&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;stream&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; context, for example:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;nginx&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1fa6d43920&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1fa6d43920&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-nginx&#34; data-lang=&#34;nginx&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;stream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;stream_backend&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;backend1.example.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;12345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;backend2.example.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;12345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;backend3.example.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;12345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-nginx&#34; data-lang=&#34;nginx&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;stream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;stream_backend&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;backend1.example.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;12345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;backend2.example.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;12345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;backend3.example.com&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;12345&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;   &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You have configured a server that passes TCP connections to the server group:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>UDP Health Checks</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/udp-health-check/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/udp-health-check/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;NGINX Plus can continually test your upstream servers that handle UDP network traffic (DNS, RADIUS, syslog), avoid the servers that have failed, and gracefully add the recovered servers into the load‑balanced group.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 &#xA;id=&#34;prereq&#34;&gt;Prerequisites  &lt;a class=&#34;headerlink float-right&#34; href=&#34;#prereq&#34; title=&#34;Prerequisites&#34;&gt;&lt;i class=&#34;fas fa-link fa-xs&#34;&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;You have &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/nginx/admin-guide/load-balancer/tcp-udp-load-balancer/&#34;&gt;configured an upstream group of servers&lt;/a&gt; that handles UDP network traffic in the &lt;a href=&#34;https://nginx.org/en/docs/stream/ngx_stream_core_module.html#stream&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;stream {}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; context, for example:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;code-block&#34; data-mf=&#34;true&#34; style=&#34;display: none;&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;code-type chroma&#34;&gt;nginx&lt;/span&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;code-container chroma&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;button onclick=&#34;copyToClipBoard(this, &amp;#34;id-18440f1fa70904c0&amp;#34;)&#34; class=&#34;code-copy-button multi-line&#34; type=&#34;button&#34;&gt;Copy&lt;/button&gt;&#xA;        &lt;div class=&#34;highlight-v2&#34; id=&#34;id-18440f1fa70904c0&#34;&gt;&#xA;            &lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-nginx&#34; data-lang=&#34;nginx&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;stream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;dns_upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;192.168.136.130&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;53&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;192.168.136.131&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;53&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;192.168.136.132&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;53&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;        &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div id=&#34;code-block-v1&#34; data-mf=&#34;false&#34;&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-nginx&#34; data-lang=&#34;nginx&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;k&#34;&gt;stream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#...&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;s&#34;&gt;dns_upstream&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;192.168.136.130&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;53&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;192.168.136.131&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;53&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;kn&#34;&gt;server&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;n&#34;&gt;192.168.136.132&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;mi&#34;&gt;53&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;c1&#34;&gt;#